        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 3:55PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Remington, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brookston, Wolcott, and Badger Grove.

This includes Interstate 65 between mile markers 185 and 198.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
